# Rolepod — Codex CLI Core Rules

Always-on guidance for the Codex CLI Lead. Codex reads this file from
`~/.codex/AGENTS.md` (global) or `<repo>/AGENTS.md` (project).

This file is heavier than the Claude `CLAUDE.md` because Codex has no native
hook system or auto-pull skill loader — gates must be inlined here so Lead
sees them every turn.

## Rule priority (when conflict)

Most-specific wins. Higher tier overrides lower:

1. User explicit instruction this turn — overrides everything
2. Project `<repo>/AGENTS.md`
3. Global `~/.codex/AGENTS.md` (this file when installed there)
4. Anthropic best practice (default if all silent)

Conflict unsafe to resolve → ask user. Don't pick silently.

